Why doesnt this just extend the DocumentTypeManagerSearchPage_DocumentTypeFolder.java from selenium FWK? In this way you can add the extra methods, without needing all the rest of the stuff!

i.e. all you need is this:

// Javadoc here
public class DocumentTypeManagerSearchPage_DocumentTypeFolder extends com.fineos.pages.DocumentTypeManagerSearchPage_DocumentTypeFolder {

	public DocumentTypeManagerSearchPage_DocumentTypeFolder(final WebDriver driver) {
		super(driver);
	}

	/**
	 * @param documentPath
	 *            The path to the event e.g. &quot;[Document Type Folders, FINEOS, Absence]&quot;
	 * @param documentName
	 *            The document name e.g. &quot;Certification Request&quot;
	 */
	public void addDocumentType(final String[] documentPath, final String documentName) {
		DocumentTypeFoldersTreeview.selectNode(documentPath);
		DocumentTypeListview.selectRow(documentName);
		OKButtonTop.click();
	}
}

